  "grammarPoint": {
    "title": "The accusative case: the object of an action",
    "explanation": "The accusative marks the thing an action is done **to** — what you watch, read, open. For **masculine and neuter inanimate nouns**, accusative looks exactly like the dictionary form: **я смотрю́ телеви́зор** (television doesn't change). For **feminine nouns ending in -а/-я**, the ending becomes **-у/-ю**: **газе́та → Я чита́ю газе́ту** (newspaper → I read a newspaper).\n\nYou already did this without knowing it — **Хочу́ во́ду** from Day 1 is exactly this rule (вода́ → во́ду).",
    "examples": [
      { "ru": "Я смотрю́ телеви́зор.", "en": "I watch television.", "note": "masc., unchanged" },
      { "ru": "Я чита́ю газе́ту.", "en": "I read a newspaper.", "note": "fem. -а → -у" },
      { "ru": "Я открыва́ю окно́.", "en": "I open the window.", "note": "neut., unchanged" },
      { "ru": "Ты берёшь кни́гу?", "en": "Are you taking the book?", "note": "fem. -а → -у" }
    ]
  },

